279
00:18:44,623 --> 00:18:50,504
[SOFT GRUNTS]

280
00:18:50,671 --> 00:18:52,506
[PHONE RINGS]

281
00:18:55,676 --> 00:18:59,221
- Yeah. What?
- Hi, Yui... It's Shogo Yahagi.

282
00:18:59,388 --> 00:19:03,058
Look, I need a big favor. Could I store something
in the parking garage at your apartment?

283
00:19:03,600 --> 00:19:06,353
- Right now.
- Right now? But why?

284
00:19:06,520 --> 00:19:11,358
- Can I explain when I get there?
I'm kinda in a hurry. - Well, sure.

285
00:19:11,525 --> 00:19:14,903
Do you know where it's at?
Right... Yeah...

286
00:19:15,070 --> 00:19:18,532
- It's a New York style, and I'll be
waiting out front. - Thanks.

287
00:19:23,787 --> 00:19:26,540
I watched that show...
and they cut you off.

288
00:19:26,707 --> 00:19:28,834
They cut me off?
But that makes no sense!

289
00:19:29,001 --> 00:19:32,212
Well that's what it looked like. You
were babbling a bunch of nonsense...

290
00:19:32,296 --> 00:19:37,342
and then the screen went blank.
Just a caption that said \"Please stand by.\"

291
00:19:38,760 --> 00:19:42,514
What's going on here? I was
talking with Eve the whole time.

292
00:19:42,681 --> 00:19:44,057
Yui: What's wrong?

293
00:19:44,224 --> 00:19:46,518
Look, I can't leave this
bike in the open.

294
00:19:46,685 --> 00:19:48,979
- The garage is in the basement.
- Thanks.

295
00:19:51,481 --> 00:19:54,484
Uhh... Sorry, the apartment
is kind of a mess.

296
00:19:54,651 --> 00:19:58,363
Nice place! But the rent
must be killer, huh?

297
00:19:58,530 --> 00:20:00,240
Yeah, for a girl on her own.

298
00:20:00,407 --> 00:20:03,869
Oh yeah, right. I totally forgot
that you had two roommates.

299
00:20:04,036 --> 00:20:06,079
- I spazzed.
- Obviously.

300
00:20:06,246 --> 00:20:09,249
- Well, have a seat and I'll make some tea.
- Great.

301
00:20:10,584 --> 00:20:12,252
- Huh...?
- Meow.

302
00:20:12,878 --> 00:20:15,714
So I guess you know what both of
my roommates are into already?

303
00:20:15,881 --> 00:20:18,425
Yeah! Tomomi wants to become
a movie director...

304
00:20:18,508 --> 00:20:20,677
and she's working on
some scripts right now.

305
00:20:20,761 --> 00:20:24,765
Mai's a singer, and she's working fill-in
at one of the Hard Rocks, right?

306
00:20:25,182 --> 00:20:27,684
Actually, she works at the
same one that I do.

307
00:20:27,768 --> 00:20:31,146
In fact, you oughta come by
and hear her sing sometime.

308
00:20:31,313 --> 00:20:34,733
If I could find the time, I would,
but my job keeps me on my feet.

309
00:20:34,900 --> 00:20:36,485
- Meow.
- Mmm-hmm.

310
00:20:37,319 --> 00:20:39,863
At McDonald's. You know,
the one on Aoyama Street.

311
00:20:40,030 --> 00:20:42,866
Really? And we're in that one,
like, all the time.

312
00:20:43,033 --> 00:20:44,993
I guess our schedules
haven't matched.

313
00:20:45,160 --> 00:20:47,329
Yui: Yeah, I guess so...

314
00:20:47,496 --> 00:20:50,874
- Myew.
- Hmmm... Hmmm...

315
00:20:51,041 --> 00:20:55,879
- So, hey, you dating anybody?
- Um, why? - Um... Just asking.

316
00:20:56,046 --> 00:20:58,298
[GETTING TO KNOW EACH OTHER MUSIC]

317
00:20:59,258 --> 00:21:02,469
But, it is cool for me to
park overnight, isn't it?

318
00:21:02,636 --> 00:21:04,972
Well, I'm not saying no.

319
00:21:08,308 --> 00:21:10,811
They're trying to kill you?

320
00:21:10,894 --> 00:21:14,273
- Are you sure?
- There's something weird about that bike.

321
00:21:14,439 --> 00:21:16,984
And that bit with the TV station proves it.

322
00:21:17,150 --> 00:21:19,069
It was strange how they cut away.

323
00:21:19,569 --> 00:21:22,364
But if it's the bike, then why
don't you just get rid of it?

324
00:21:22,531 --> 00:21:25,951
Too late now. And, to be
perfectly honest...

325
00:21:26,118 --> 00:21:30,289
even though it's scary, I just can't let
whatever happened to Shinji go unanswered.

326
00:21:31,206 --> 00:21:32,582
So now it's personal.

327
00:21:32,749 --> 00:21:35,752
But it's more than that.
It just wouldn't be right.

328
00:21:35,919 --> 00:21:39,131
Yeah, know what you mean.
And there's more.

329
00:21:39,214 --> 00:21:42,467
There's a kind of rush that you feel when
you're putting everything on the line.

330
00:21:43,093 --> 00:21:45,554
- You get it.
- I've been around.

331
00:21:45,721 --> 00:21:49,099
Still, there's never been a better
place or time to be alive.

332
00:21:49,683 --> 00:21:52,477
Yui: Sometimes I think it's
the best it'll ever be.

333
00:21:52,936 --> 00:21:55,105
It... feels good.

334
00:21:55,272 --> 00:21:58,317
- Better than sex?
- Oh, please!

335
00:22:00,694 --> 00:22:02,237
So what's your blood type?

336
00:22:02,404 --> 00:22:04,239
[SCOFFS] You gonna ask my sign next?

337
00:22:04,406 --> 00:22:06,074
It helps me understand you.

338
00:22:06,241 --> 00:22:10,829
- I'm a B. - B? I see. Well,
I don't normally hate type B...

339
00:22:10,912 --> 00:22:13,623
especially ones who get
too worked up about silly things.

340
00:22:15,083 --> 00:22:18,045
- Was I just zinged?
- [LAUGHS]

341
00:22:18,378 --> 00:22:22,299
- Shogo: I was! You! Hey, come back here!
- Yui: See, you're getting all worked up!

342
00:22:24,509 --> 00:22:27,304
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

343
00:22:27,471 --> 00:22:28,847
Hey! What's up?

344
00:22:29,014 --> 00:22:33,352
Uh, just hangin'. And I was thinkin'
that if you didn't have to work...

345
00:22:33,518 --> 00:22:35,187
maybe you'd like to go somewhere.

346
00:22:35,354 --> 00:22:39,608
Yui: Oh, um, sorry, I'm on my way
to a gig at the TV station.

347
00:22:39,775 --> 00:22:41,902
- Shogo: Do you have to?
- Yui: Yeah.

348
00:22:42,069 --> 00:22:44,363
It's not much,
but a girl's got to eat.

349
00:22:44,529 --> 00:22:46,948
And it's my chance to make
some real connections.

350
00:22:47,032 --> 00:22:50,535
You may laugh at this, but it's my dream
to stand on a Broadway stage.

351
00:22:50,702 --> 00:22:52,996
Shogo: Oh, no. I think that's great.

352
00:22:53,163 --> 00:22:56,666
- Yui: Hey, if you wanted to come...
- Shogo: To the TV station?

353
00:22:56,833 --> 00:22:59,836
Yeah, I've always wanted
to see inside one of those.

354
00:22:59,920 --> 00:23:01,922
Sure, I'll come.

355
00:23:02,964 --> 00:23:07,260
[DANCE BEAT]

356
00:23:17,604 --> 00:23:19,314
Hmm...?

357
00:23:35,664 --> 00:23:36,957
