- Right! - Eyaah!

435
00:29:26,389 --> 00:29:29,517
- Looks like we lost him.
- What's the deal with this empty tunnel?

436
00:29:29,684 --> 00:29:31,936
- [RUMBLING]
- [YELPS OF SURPRISE]

437
00:29:33,521 --> 00:29:36,524
Hey! What's happening?!

438
00:29:37,233 --> 00:29:39,152
Huh...?

439
00:29:39,235 --> 00:29:42,238
Hey wait, it's going up now.
But how...?

440
00:29:51,247 --> 00:29:53,208
Well, at least we lost the cop, huh?

441
00:29:53,374 --> 00:29:54,959
[GRUNTS] Ow!

442
00:29:55,126 --> 00:29:56,878
What'd you stop for?

443
00:29:58,171 --> 00:29:59,380
Huh?

444
00:29:59,547 --> 00:30:02,300
[SUSPENSEFUL, MYSTERIOUS MUSIC]

445
00:30:16,689 --> 00:30:20,610
Hey... there's a town
up on the ceiling, too.

446
00:30:21,444 --> 00:30:25,114
It's like the world's biggest
ghost town, inside a funhouse.

447
00:30:28,284 --> 00:30:31,287
There's some lights over there.
That must be where the people are.

448
00:30:38,503 --> 00:30:43,049
B.D.: We've cleared through Bahamut 6. Currently
we're in the process of cracking level 7G.

449
00:30:43,216 --> 00:30:47,095
- Hey, that's his voice! - Fortunately,
I don't think the man who stole the bike...

450
00:30:47,178 --> 00:30:49,180
understood its connection
with Bahamut.

451
00:30:49,347 --> 00:30:51,516
Superior Officer: Good.
If it becomes known that...

452
00:30:51,599 --> 00:30:54,769
Bahamut is a computer that
oversees this time period...

453
00:30:54,853 --> 00:30:57,272
the military's plans will
be severely impaired.

454
00:30:57,689 --> 00:31:01,109
So Bahamut is the name of
some kind of computer?

455
00:31:01,276 --> 00:31:05,446
B.D.: And even if those street punks did learn
that the bike is a terminal for Bahamut...

456
00:31:05,530 --> 00:31:08,199
- they could never understand it.
- Oh, wow!

457
00:31:08,366 --> 00:31:10,535
So Bahamut's a big computer?

458
00:31:10,702 --> 00:31:13,788
This is getting heavy.
You should go.

459
00:31:13,955 --> 00:31:19,252
Hmm... Well, I got the whole thing on film,
so maybe I should leave. What about you?

460
00:31:19,419 --> 00:31:22,755
After I've scoped this
place out. See ya.

461
00:31:34,434 --> 00:31:37,478
Looks like some of the elevators
go all the way up.

462
00:31:59,042 --> 00:32:01,628
Why is it getting so cold?

463
00:32:11,804 --> 00:32:14,807
[GASPS]

464
00:32:19,437 --> 00:32:24,067
I don't get it. How can the gravity here be
pulling up and down at the same time?

465
00:32:34,786 --> 00:32:38,122
Rogue Garland sighted in Block A3.
Send Hargan Unit to A2.

466
00:32:38,498 --> 00:32:39,624
Oh shit!

467
00:32:41,209 --> 00:32:43,670
Robot bike, don't fail me now!

468
00:32:53,638 --> 00:32:56,349
Damn, they're cutting me off!

469
00:32:57,058 --> 00:32:58,893
Soldier: Come on out and surrender!

470
00:33:00,520 --> 00:33:02,605
[SCREAMS]

471
00:33:22,750 --> 00:33:25,420
- God dammit!
- I'm not dead yet!

472
00:33:28,381 --> 00:33:30,258
What the hell?
Now I'm in space?!

473
00:33:30,425 --> 00:33:33,219
[MYSTERIOUS MUSIC]

474
00:33:41,686 --> 00:33:44,772
I can't believe that punk
has come this far!

475
00:33:50,028 --> 00:33:52,530
Stop rotating so I can get a shot!

476
00:33:55,158 --> 00:33:57,285
What the?!

477
00:34:02,582 --> 00:34:04,782
Why don't you just give up on
the damn grappling lines?!

478
00:34:04,834 --> 00:34:07,545
Wait! How about if we just
stand down and talk, OK?

479
00:34:07,712 --> 00:34:10,590
Then lose the gun! And don't
go trying any funny shit!

480
00:34:10,965 --> 00:34:13,217
I'm ready for some answers here.

481
00:34:21,225 --> 00:34:23,394
[RAPID PANTING]

482
00:34:26,898 --> 00:34:29,650
A secret metropolis buried
beneath the Earth?

483
00:34:29,734 --> 00:34:32,153
Or a movie set just
waiting to be filmed?

484
00:34:32,695 --> 00:34:37,075
Can a girl ask for a better place to shoot
her feature debut? [CHORTLES]

485
00:34:37,158 --> 00:34:39,118
Wow!

486
00:34:40,244 --> 00:34:42,080
It's time to start talking.

487
00:34:43,331 --> 00:34:45,124
Why have you been chasing me?

488
00:34:45,291 --> 00:34:47,502
Why did you just help me?

489
00:34:47,960 --> 00:34:49,712
You already knew the
truth, didn't you?

490
00:34:49,796 --> 00:34:53,132
That our whole city's actually
inside a giant spaceship.

491
00:34:53,299 --> 00:34:56,469
That's correct. The military
has known for quite a while.

492
00:34:56,636 --> 00:35:01,557
- But...? - But it's not the military
that's been hiding all of this.

493
00:35:01,641 --> 00:35:03,976
Bahamut is the one who
didn't want us to know!

494
00:35:04,602 --> 00:35:07,480
Yeah, Bahamut...
What the hell is that thing?

495
00:35:07,647 --> 00:35:12,318
A computer. One that's been secretly controlling
everything the human race sees and hears...

496
00:35:12,401 --> 00:35:14,195
since before we were born.

497
00:35:14,278 --> 00:35:18,157
It's manipulated us so skillfully
that we'd never realize the truth.

498
00:35:18,241 --> 00:35:23,246
Which is that the city we live in is
actually part of a giant spaceship.

499
00:35:23,329 --> 00:35:25,748
All of this so that except
for an elite few...

500
00:35:25,832 --> 00:35:30,670
the populus would be blissfully living
in an illusion of the perfect world.

501
00:35:30,753 --> 00:35:33,923
Or rather, the perfect prison.

502
00:35:34,090 --> 00:35:37,844
So everything else, the rest of the world,
exists only in the computer?

503
00:35:38,010 --> 00:35:42,014
And the time we think we live
in is five centuries past.

504
00:35:44,142 --> 00:35:46,811
Five centuries...?

505
00:35:47,186 --> 00:35:49,939
No! That's totally crazy!

506
00:35:50,022 --> 00:35:52,650
And I don't remember giving
you permission to move!

507
00:35:52,817 --> 00:35:54,694
Lemme show you something.

508
00:35:54,777 --> 00:35:56,863
- Follow me.
- I said stop!

509
00:35:59,198 --> 00:36:01,033
Oh, don't be afraid.

510
00:36:03,786 --> 00:36:08,332
[INTRIGUESQUE MUSIC]

511
00:36:20,386 --> 00:36:24,348
This base is our frontline against
any alien infiltrations.

512
00:36:24,515 --> 00:36:25,515
What?

513
00:36:25,558 --> 00:36:30,479
Our radar's detected an enormous artificial
construct approaching this ship's position.

514
00:36:31,272 --> 00:36:35,401
And that means this false peace
we live in is going to end.

515
00:36:35,568 --> 00:36:38,654
- My god...
- [SCOFFS] Welcome to reality.

516
00:36:38,821 --> 00:36:40,698
But how do you know
they're our enemy?

517
00:36:40,865 --> 00:36:42,867
You saw that molten wasteland?

518
00:36:43,034 --> 00:36:47,622
That's the reality of the impending danger
that we are all now exposed to.

519
00:36:47,705 --> 00:36:50,541
Which is why we've secretly
expanded our military...

520
00:36:50,625 --> 00:36:52,668
and developed new
weapons projects...

521
00:36:52,752 --> 00:36:57,215
here, underground, where
Bahamut's influence can't reach us.

522
00:36:57,298 --> 00:37:02,386
That's why we've been trying to find the key
to overriding Bahamut's core directives.

523
00:37:02,470 --> 00:37:06,224
Thus far, we've managed to clear
six levels of programming.

524
00:37:06,307 --> 00:37:10,019
That left just level seven. However,
before we could clear it...

525
00:37:10,102 --> 00:37:14,482
the Garland interface unit that we had
secretly been developing was stolen.

526
00:37:14,565 --> 00:37:17,151
That bike that you've been joy-riding on.

527
00:37:17,318 --> 00:37:23,157
It wasn't supposed to be revealed until we were
on the verge of cracking the seventh level.

528
00:37:23,407 --> 00:37:27,620
So that's how it is. And the second
Bahamut falls into your grimy hands...

529
00:37:27,703 --> 00:37:30,164
you'll be able to do whatever
you want without challenge!

530
00:37:30,331 --> 00:37:33,626
No one in the city will even know
until the war breaks out!

531
00:37:34,043 --> 00:37:37,129
And you are going to let us
take advantage of that.

532
00:37:37,296 --> 00:37:38,923
[SCOFFS]

533
00:37:39,090 --> 00:37:44,595
I'm giving you the choice of becoming one
of my right-hand men, or death at my hands.

534
00:37:44,762 --> 00:37:46,889
Yeah, right.

535
00:37:46,973 --> 00:37:50,351
I'd like to see you try it!

536
00:37:56,399 --> 00:37:58,317
[ECHOING GUNSHOT]

537
00:37:59,902 --> 00:38:01,779
[MOTORCYCLE STARTS]

538
00:38:15,793 --> 00:38:17,086
[SCOFFS]

539
00:38:23,342 --> 00:38:24,760
[ENERGETIC DANCE MUSIC]

540
00:38:32,435 --> 00:38:33,728
Yui: Hey, Tomomi. What's up?

541
00:38:33,894 --> 00:38:37,189
Tomomi: Would you stop acting so
mopey and just call him yourself?

542
00:38:37,356 --> 00:38:38,524
Yui: That's why you called?

543
00:38:38,691 --> 00:38:42,236
Tomomi: You know, when I said I wanted
to make a movie, I was serious.

544
00:38:42,403 --> 00:38:44,322
Un-huh... And so?

545
00:38:44,488 --> 00:38:49,327
Tomomi: And, I really am going to use him
for the lead. Is that all right with you?

546
00:38:49,952 --> 00:38:53,789
[SIGHS] Hey look, you're the director.
You do what you want.

547
00:38:53,956 --> 00:38:59,462
Tomomi: Awesome! In that case, I wanna have a
story meeting tonight! Will you call him for me?

548
00:38:59,628 --> 00:39:01,630
Me call him?!

549
00:39:04,967 --> 00:39:07,053
Tomomi: So, this is the idea.

550
00:39:07,136 --> 00:39:10,306
- There's this guy, see, who likes
motorcycles and stuff. - Meow!

551
00:39:10,389 --> 00:39:13,017
But then, one day, he and his
girlfriend discover that...

552
00:39:13,100 --> 00:39:17,438
everything in their world has been
fabricated by a giant computer.

553
00:39:17,521 --> 00:39:19,774
And the next part is the
real hilight of the film.

554
00:39:20,274 --> 00:39:23,277
The two of them have their lives
threatened by unknown assailants...

555
00:39:23,361 --> 00:39:25,279
and unbeknownst to
the rest of the world...

556
00:39:25,363 --> 00:39:29,825
they smash a secret organization
that's trying to create a military state!

557
00:39:30,576 --> 00:39:31,994
Or something like that.

558
00:39:32,078 --> 00:39:33,996
- How's that?
- Hmm...

559
00:39:34,163 --> 00:39:38,209
The thing is that I can barely afford
the film stock, so I need your help.

560
00:39:38,292 --> 00:39:40,211
Are you guys with me?

561
00:39:42,630 --> 00:39:44,548
Sure. I'll do what I can.

562
00:39:44,715 --> 00:39:49,929
So, how about you, Shogo?
You'd be the perfect leading man.

563
00:39:50,638 --> 00:39:52,890
You don't want to play
opposite me, do you?

564
00:39:54,600 --> 00:39:56,852
You don't want anything
to do with me.

565
00:39:56,936 --> 00:39:58,938
You won't even tell me where
you're working now.

566
00:39:59,021 --> 00:40:01,440
You won't speak.
It's like I'm not there.

567
00:40:01,524 --> 00:40:03,859
I never should have bothered
calling you, should I?

568
00:40:04,026 --> 00:40:06,529
Actually, I wanted to call you too.

569
00:40:06,695 --> 00:40:07,488
[SOFT GASP]

570
00:40:07,655 --> 00:40:10,491
And my problem's not with
you being in the movie.

571
00:40:11,117 --> 00:40:14,328
I've just... got a bad
feeling about this.

572
00:40:14,495 --> 00:40:15,996
[DOOR OPENING]

573
00:40:16,956 --> 00:40:21,127
- Mai: Tadah Tum Tadah! Yeah!
- Tomomi: Oh, hi Mai! Holy cow, what's that?

574
00:40:21,293 --> 00:40:24,547
I'm so freaked!
You won't believe this!

575
00:40:24,713 --> 00:40:29,552
My agent just got me my first recording
gig, and I'm singing backup for Eve!

576
00:40:29,927 --> 00:40:32,930
- No shit!
- That's wonderful, Mai!

577
00:40:33,097 --> 00:40:36,892
- I've been scouted. - That's awesome.
It's your chance to hit it big.

578
00:40:37,059 --> 00:40:39,019
- Mai: Yeah!
- [JOYFUL SQUEALS]

579
00:40:39,186 --> 00:40:42,022
And the best part is that
Eve's your favorite singer.

580
00:40:42,189 --> 00:40:44,400
- Thank you, god!
- [SIGHS] Later, OK?

581
00:40:44,567 --> 00:40:49,029
- Huh? Oh wow, was I interrupting something?
- You're leaving?

582
00:40:49,196 --> 00:40:51,866
Hey wait, why don't we go out
and party? My treat!

583
00:40:52,032 --> 00:40:55,744
Tomomi: Yeah, and I wanna talk some
more about the movie, too. C'mon!

584
00:40:55,911 --> 00:40:58,539
Shogo: Oh, yeah? Well,
how 'bout this one?

585
00:40:58,706 --> 00:40:59,707
Huh?

586
00:40:59,874 --> 00:41:04,795
What if the entire world that we live in
was being controlled from outside.

587
00:41:04,879 --> 00:41:07,923
What if everything was an illusion,
run by a computer...

588
00:41:09,258 --> 00:41:11,719
that also controls
a giant spaceship.

589
00:41:11,886 --> 00:41:15,139
- A spaceship?
- Umm, did I miss something here?

590
00:41:15,306 --> 00:41:20,352
In other words, what if this city was inside
some gigantic ship, floating in space?

591
00:41:20,519 --> 00:41:22,897
Hmm... Sci-fi is hot...

592
00:41:23,063 --> 00:41:25,107
Yeah, it's just something
I thought of.

593
00:41:25,191 --> 00:41:28,068
- Interesting, huh?
- [MYSTERIOUS, CONSPIRATORIAL MUSIC]

594
00:41:32,448 --> 00:41:35,075
General: We can't fight a war
with these relics.

595
00:41:35,159 --> 00:41:37,411
What's the status on
Airgrain FX production?

596
00:41:37,703 --> 00:41:40,873
The fact that we can't work on the surface
is hindering construction.

597
00:41:40,956 --> 00:41:43,292
We're making progress,
but we're losing time.

598
00:41:43,459 --> 00:41:45,377
It's always Bahamut.

599
00:41:45,544 --> 00:41:48,797
We have currently cleared
seventy percent of level seven.

600
00:41:48,881 --> 00:41:50,925
The rest is just a matter of time.

601
00:41:51,091 --> 00:41:55,679
General: Time that we don't have.
That unidentified object is approaching.

602
00:41:55,846 --> 00:41:59,350
- I understand, sir.
- Just get it done!

603
00:42:04,396 --> 00:42:07,274
[CAR STARTS, DEPARTS]

604
00:42:09,318 --> 00:42:14,740
All talk and no backbone. When it comes down to
the wire, I know which way they'll be running.

605
00:42:14,907 --> 00:42:17,201
My men feel exactly the same way.

606
00:42:17,368 --> 00:42:22,081
After all, how can we trust a leadership corps
who only cares about saving their own skins?

607
00:42:22,164 --> 00:42:23,791
Too bad we're not in charge.

608
00:42:23,958 --> 00:42:29,129
Oh, our time will come-
if we have to make it ourselves!

609
00:42:29,463 --> 00:42:32,091
[ADVENTUROUS MUSIC]

610
00:42:32,383 --> 00:42:35,386
It's OK, I won't ask you any
more questions about it.

611
00:42:35,553 --> 00:42:38,847
- Look, I'd like to tell you, but-
- No, really, it's cool.

612
00:42:39,014 --> 00:42:41,475
Fantastic, this is awesome!

613
00:42:45,813 --> 00:42:48,524
This is going to be great!

614
00:42:51,026 --> 00:42:54,071
- Is that story for real?
- That's what Mai told me.

615
00:42:54,238 --> 00:42:58,993
But that doesn't make sense! Why wouldn't a big
star like Eve show up for her own session?

616
00:42:59,159 --> 00:43:00,703
Yeah, Mai was really bummed out.

617
00:43:00,869 --> 00:43:03,455
And how will they do
the video with only Mai?

618
00:43:03,622 --> 00:43:07,126
They said that they'd cut them
together, but there's more.

619
00:43:07,293 --> 00:43:08,877
- Something odd.
- What's that?

620
00:43:09,044 --> 00:43:13,924
No one's ever seen Eve except on TV.
No concerts or anything.

621
00:43:38,699 --> 00:43:40,701
[POP MUSIC (FAINT)]

622
00:43:49,668 --> 00:43:56,717
~b~Eve: ~i~Those who are dreaming...
Lips...

623
00:43:57,760 --> 00:44:05,184
Hesitant hearts... Fingertips...

624
00:44:05,267 --> 00:44:09,146
Chase the wind...

625
00:44:09,229 --> 00:44:13,150
and seize hold of love...

626
00:44:13,233 --> 00:44:20,366
before this blue city crumbles to dust.

627
00:44:21,033 --> 00:44:27,164
The sky, reflected in building windows...

628
00:44:27,331 --> 00:44:28,999
Technician A: Hold on! Stop recording!

629
00:44:29,291 --> 00:44:31,293
[STATIC]

630
00:44:31,835 --> 00:44:34,838
We're supposed to rewind by
three seconds, seven frames.

631
00:44:35,005 --> 00:44:37,132
Technician B: Yeah, yeah, all right.

632
00:44:38,384 --> 00:44:41,303
Technician B: Man, this
computer is just amazing!

633
00:44:41,470 --> 00:44:44,556
Technician A: Yeah, generating the melody
and the lyrics simultaneously.

634
00:44:44,723 --> 00:44:49,603
Technician A: Then we have to redo it because
they screwed up the choreography. Figures!

635
00:44:49,770 --> 00:44:50,770
[BOTH LAUGH]

636
00:44:50,813 --> 00:44:53,893
Technician A: It doesn't matter. This song
will be a hit too. They always are.

637
00:44:53,982 --> 00:45:01,982
~b~Eve: ~i~The sky,
reflected in building windows...

638
00:45:02,241 --> 00:45:03,784
wants to...

639
00:45:03,951 --> 00:45:05,869
[DRAMATIC GUITAR LINE]

640
00:45:12,793 --> 00:45:16,422
Everyone... they've been
fooling everyone!

641
00:45:19,007 --> 00:45:21,093
Lousy kid!

642
00:45:21,385 --> 00:45:25,222
- Hey Todd, you wanna check out my VCR?
- Sure. - [BOTH SCREAM]

643
00:45:25,764 --> 00:45:27,933
I don't think so, coppers!

644
00:45:39,153 --> 00:45:40,696
[SCREAMS]

645
00:45:40,863 --> 00:45:42,823
Ahhh!

646
00:45:46,702 --> 00:45:48,662
[SCREAMS]

647
00:46:03,635 --> 00:46:06,346
[PHONE BEEPS]

648
00:46:06,513 --> 00:46:08,974
[GROANS SLEEPILY]

649
00:46:11,852 --> 00:46:14,021
Yeah, B.D.

650
00:46:14,104 --> 00:46:16,774
What?! He drop-kicked a cop car?

651
00:46:16,940 --> 00:46:18,860
Subordinate: That's right;
in the middle of town.

652
00:46:18,942 --> 00:46:21,570
He's on the other line, and
demanding to speak with you.

653
00:46:21,737 --> 00:46:23,864
What the hell.
Put him through.

654
00:46:24,031 --> 00:46:26,241
Subordinate: Yes, sir. Connecting.

655
00:46:30,120 --> 00:46:34,416
- Shogo: Hey, it's me.
- Well. Causing a little commotion, are we?

656
00:46:34,958 --> 00:46:38,921
Maybe. Do you know that singer,
Eve? Interesting woman.

657
00:46:39,004 --> 00:46:41,757
- In fact, I just met her.
- B.D.: And...?

658
00:46:41,924 --> 00:46:44,927
And I think it's time you stopped
making fools of everyone!

659
00:46:45,093 --> 00:46:49,556
That's all very nice, kid, but you're
barking up the wrong tree.

660
00:46:49,640 --> 00:46:52,476
B.D.: Eve isn't our creation,
she's Bahamut's.

661
00:46:52,643 --> 00:46:54,186
I'm goin' public anyway!

662
00:46:54,353 --> 00:46:57,523
B.D.: [CHUCKLES]
Oh, we'll see about that.

663
00:46:57,606 --> 00:47:00,526
Remember what happened when
you called the TV station?

664
00:47:00,943 --> 00:47:02,778
- So that was you...
- [POLICE SIREN]

665
00:47:02,945 --> 00:47:04,029
[GRUNTS]

666
00:47:04,112 --> 00:47:07,407
Well just because you've got the media
locked up in the palm of your hand...

667
00:47:07,491 --> 00:47:10,244
doesn't mean you're
gonna be safe!

668
00:47:10,494 --> 00:47:12,412
[HANGUP TONE]

669
00:47:18,669 --> 00:47:20,587
[DRAMATIC, SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

670
00:47:27,553 --> 00:47:30,472
I want a full status update.
Distance?

671
00:47:30,639 --> 00:47:33,267
Reading 400 as of the
last capture count.

672
00:47:33,433 --> 00:47:38,605
There's no doubt; the target code-named
Dezalg is definitely on an intercept vector.

673
00:47:38,772 --> 00:47:42,985
That fast. And where do we stand on
the Bahamut decryption process?

674
00:47:43,151 --> 00:47:48,532
According to the latest report, the data technicians
are still examining the control codes for level seven.

675
00:47:48,699 --> 00:47:51,368
- Well, tell them to work faster!
- Yes, sir.

676
00:47:51,535 --> 00:47:55,956
Supervisor: Voice command and statement
from level seven has been changed to E.V.E.

677
00:47:56,123 --> 00:47:58,041
Please confirm your memory maps.

678
00:48:04,840 --> 00:48:07,301
There it is! I've finally
found it, sir.

679
00:48:07,384 --> 00:48:12,556
The EVE interpreter is recorded
in the slave ROM; area AD3 to 9F3!

680
00:48:12,723 --> 00:48:17,686
All right, all we have to do now use the
machine language and convert it to our own.

681
