901
01:03:52,745 --> 01:03:55,957
Umm... Well... I don't like being
called a private, y'know...

902
01:03:56,040 --> 01:04:00,211
but I'll get a stylin' uniform,
and a gun! That'll be cool!

903
01:04:00,294 --> 01:04:03,381
And, it's for our country!
Whatever! [LAUGHS]

904
01:04:03,464 --> 01:04:06,777
- Morley... - And that's Chombo behind him.
- Newslady: Thank you very much, and good luck.

905
01:04:06,801 --> 01:04:10,596
- Newslady: how about you? - I was wondering
where those two knuckleheads were.

906
01:04:10,680 --> 01:04:12,807
Damn! What the hell
were they thinking?!

907
01:04:20,982 --> 01:04:24,819
So, the last I heard, you were
singing with Eve. Is that still a go?

908
01:04:24,986 --> 01:04:30,700
Uh-huh. But it's actually pretty boring. All we've
been recording is that military propaganda.

909
01:04:32,076 --> 01:04:34,078
- Where's Tomomi?
- Yui: [SIGHS]

910
01:04:34,245 --> 01:04:37,874
When she's editing a film, I don't
think Tomomi even sleeps.

911
01:04:37,957 --> 01:04:40,418
She asked if we could bring her
some burgers and beer.

912
01:04:40,585 --> 01:04:44,755
Man, if she keeps this up,
she'll look like a keg!

913
01:04:44,922 --> 01:04:46,924
[DOG BARKS]

914
01:04:49,385 --> 01:04:53,514
Oh, yeah... cool... cool!

915
01:04:54,056 --> 01:04:57,560
Mmmm... And the composite
images turned out great, too!

916
01:04:57,643 --> 01:05:00,730
Perfect! Nobody's gonna
believe this film!

917
01:05:07,695 --> 01:05:11,240
- [CHORTLE] - [CLATTER]
- Huh...? Mai?

918
01:05:11,407 --> 01:05:13,284
[GASPS]

919
01:05:14,118 --> 01:05:17,455
- Who are you?! What're you-
- [SILENCED GUNSHOT] - [CHOKED YELP]

920
01:05:17,622 --> 01:05:20,708
But... why?

921
01:05:22,835 --> 01:05:25,838
[DRAMATIC STRUMS]

922
01:05:32,553 --> 01:05:34,639
[CONSPIRATORIAL PIANO]

923
01:05:42,355 --> 01:05:43,940
Loose end eliminated.

924
01:05:44,106 --> 01:05:48,903
Excellent. Make sure you retrieve the
negatives and any incriminating evidence.

925
01:05:48,986 --> 01:05:50,988
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

926
01:05:53,366 --> 01:05:56,243
[SHOCKED WAIL]

927
01:05:56,661 --> 01:05:59,705
[DRAMATIC NOTE]

928
01:05:59,872 --> 01:06:03,000
- [ANGUISHED GASPS]
- T-Tomomi...

929
01:06:03,167 --> 01:06:05,544
- Oh my god! Is she...?
- [MELANCHOLY PIANO]

930
01:06:08,923 --> 01:06:13,928
- No! [WAILS] No! No!
- Mai!

931
01:06:22,770 --> 01:06:25,439
Him!

932
01:06:26,649 --> 01:06:28,526
Where are you going?!

933
01:06:28,859 --> 01:06:32,530
I can't tell you.
But I'll be back, I promise.

934
01:06:32,697 --> 01:06:34,949
Shogo...

935
01:06:41,747 --> 01:06:44,875
[WEEPING]

936
01:06:50,548 --> 01:06:52,633
Mai...

937
01:06:52,717 --> 01:06:56,095
We've got to hold it together, Mai.
We need to call the police.

938
01:06:56,262 --> 01:06:58,556
[PHONE RINGS]

939
01:07:05,229 --> 01:07:08,733
Yes? Yes, sir, I...

940
01:07:08,816 --> 01:07:12,528
She's here, but I-
Yes, sir, I'll put her on now.

941
01:07:12,611 --> 01:07:16,657
Mai! Your father wants
to speak to you.

942
01:07:17,825 --> 01:07:21,829
- [SOBS] Yes, Papa? - Yumekano: Mai!
- That's right, it's me, Papa...

943
01:07:21,996 --> 01:07:25,458
Yumekano: Thank god. We've been looking
everywhere for you. Are you all right?

944
01:07:25,541 --> 01:07:27,585
- Your mother's very worried.
- Uh-huh.

945
01:07:27,752 --> 01:07:31,130
Mai, I think it's time
you came home.

946
01:07:31,213 --> 01:07:35,468
The world's going to be changing,
and things will become... difficult.

947
01:07:35,551 --> 01:07:38,179
You can't go on living
day-to-day anymore.

948
01:07:38,262 --> 01:07:42,475
- I won't insist, but I really wish you'd
come back where you belong. - [LOUD WEEPING]

949
01:07:42,558 --> 01:07:44,935
Oh, Papa!

950
01:07:45,102 --> 01:07:49,607
[ACTIVE, DRAMATIC MUSIC]

951
01:07:49,774 --> 01:07:52,068
I'm coming for you, you bastard!

952
01:07:52,234 --> 01:07:55,863
We've made a thorough examination of
the captured enemy patrol ship...

953
01:07:55,946 --> 01:08:00,451
and from the data we've collected, it seems that
their weaponry is fifty years ahead of ours.

954
01:08:02,870 --> 01:08:06,165
True, but at this point we have
no option left but to fight.

955
01:08:06,332 --> 01:08:11,170
With luck, we should be able to reverse-
engineer some of their weapons fairly quickly.

956
01:08:11,587 --> 01:08:15,382
But their full capabilities are still
unknown. How can we plan for that?

957
01:08:15,716 --> 01:08:20,429
Our records show that five hundred years
ago, our forces were evenly matched.

958
01:08:20,513 --> 01:08:24,558
However, with a fifty-year technological
lag in armaments, and...

959
01:08:24,642 --> 01:08:28,312
a probable numerical disadvantage
as well, I believe that we need...

960
01:08:28,395 --> 01:08:33,651
to seriously reconsider our current strategy
if there is to be any chance of winning.

961
01:08:34,693 --> 01:08:37,571
We've chosen our course,
and there's no turning back!

962
01:08:37,655 --> 01:08:40,658
Therefore, think only of what
will lead us to victory!

963
01:08:40,908 --> 01:08:42,618
I'm sorry, sir.

964
01:08:42,785 --> 01:08:45,745
- Destroying Bahamut oughta piss him off!
- Headband: \"Victory at Any Cost\"

965
01:08:47,706 --> 01:08:50,501
Turkey One to Full House.
Intruder is in B1.

966
01:08:50,584 --> 01:08:53,379
Advancing towards Bahamut.
Requesting Hargan backup.

967
01:08:53,546 --> 01:08:54,713
Full House: Roger.

968
01:08:57,675 --> 01:08:59,802
- Watch this!
- [ACTION MUSIC]

969
01:09:03,097 --> 01:09:05,474
Turkey Two: Yeah! All right!

970
01:09:05,808 --> 01:09:09,353
He's dead; nothing on the sensors.
I'm going down to confirm.

971
01:09:09,520 --> 01:09:13,149
Hey, wait! It's still dangerous.
Get back up here!

972
01:09:17,570 --> 01:09:20,072
[SCREAMS]

973
01:09:20,447 --> 01:09:24,285
Uhh! Turkey One to Balbrun!
The target is using sensor reduction.

974
01:09:24,368 --> 01:09:27,955
We lost visual contact just short
of Highway 28 in Block A5.

975
01:09:28,122 --> 01:09:32,126
Lawson: Balbrun Leader to all units.
The target is headed our way.

976
01:09:32,209 --> 01:09:36,422
Set down and assume Formation One.
Shoot to kill on sight.

977
01:09:36,589 --> 01:09:37,673
Soldier A: Roger.

978
01:09:37,840 --> 01:09:40,176
Energy reading at 12 o'clock.

979
01:09:40,342 --> 01:09:43,679
Soldier B: Thermal signature approaching.
Get out of its trajectory, now!

980
01:09:45,181 --> 01:09:48,809
- Lawson: That was him. - Soldier A: Full speed
along the trajectory? I don't believe it!

981
01:09:48,976 --> 01:09:51,496
- Lawson: You'd better believe it!
- Soldier A: I'm sorry, sir...

982
01:09:51,520 --> 01:09:53,290
but he's managed to break
through to Bahamut.

983
01:09:53,314 --> 01:09:58,235
- B.D.: This is ridiculous! - Lawson: Request
permission to use weapons inside Bahamut.

984
01:09:58,444 --> 01:10:01,447
At a time like this,
that pathetic little-

985
01:10:01,697 --> 01:10:06,243
- Permission for Energy Swords only. And
don't let him get away! - Officer: Yes, sir!

986
01:10:06,410 --> 01:10:09,788
OK, so this screwed-up world
is all your fault, huh?

987
01:10:14,835 --> 01:10:16,253
What?! Out of ammo?!

988
01:10:16,337 --> 01:10:18,339
Ah, geez! And here they come!

989
01:10:21,425 --> 01:10:24,345
Huh...? What is this?

990
01:10:24,511 --> 01:10:26,972
[SCREAMS]

991
01:10:27,139 --> 01:10:29,767
Oh, shit! [CHOKED SCREAM]

992
01:10:30,184 --> 01:10:32,770
- There he is! - Mackie's down.
- Don't let him get away!

993
01:10:36,982 --> 01:10:39,235
Damn! Where is that bastard?
[GRUNTS]

994
01:10:39,652 --> 01:10:41,445
Can't take much more!

995
01:10:41,612 --> 01:10:44,615
[MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

996
01:10:46,659 --> 01:10:49,078
Aha! There you are!

997
01:10:49,245 --> 01:10:51,413
B.D.: I see you recognize me, Yahagi.

998
01:10:51,497 --> 01:10:55,459
I can't trust you to those incompetents.
Care for a piece of me?

999
01:10:55,542 --> 01:10:58,629
You have no idea what this
world's really fighting!

1000
01:10:58,796 --> 01:11:01,340
Damn, he's good.
This won't be easy.

1001
01:11:01,423 --> 01:11:03,550
But I'm too damn stubborn to lose!

1002
01:11:03,717 --> 01:11:07,096
- Don't get too cocky, kid!
- Screw you!

1003
01:11:07,263 --> 01:11:10,432
B.D.: You'd better learn to aim first!

1004
01:11:11,684 --> 01:11:14,019
Aww, what's wrong,
no more bullets?

1005
01:11:14,186 --> 01:11:17,690
- I'm not the pushover you think I am!
- B.D.: Oh, yeah? Well, how's this?!

1006
01:11:21,610 --> 01:11:23,529
B.D.: Where's your
cocky attitude now, kid?

1007
01:11:23,696 --> 01:11:25,698
[GASPS]

1008
01:11:31,370 --> 01:11:35,416
What happened to all that fire
you just had? Get on your feet!

1009
01:11:35,582 --> 01:11:37,710
Now you know how tough
you really are.

1010
01:11:37,793 --> 01:11:40,254
And by the way,
I owe ya something!

1011
01:11:41,547 --> 01:11:42,131
[GRUNTS]

1012
01:11:42,214 --> 01:11:44,049
[SCREAMS]

1013
01:11:47,803 --> 01:11:50,764
This fight is over. All units,
return to the line.

1014
01:11:50,931 --> 01:11:53,684
Major, a second enemy
wave is approaching.

1015
01:11:53,851 --> 01:11:55,728
Roger. I'm on my way.

1016
01:11:57,104 --> 01:12:00,941
[GRANDFATHER CLOCK CHIMES 4AM]

1017
01:12:19,376 --> 01:12:21,170
[SOFT SOBS]

1018
01:12:21,253 --> 01:12:24,381
I'm sorry...

1019
01:12:24,465 --> 01:12:29,345
I'm sorry, Yui!
I'm so sorry. [SOBS]

1020
01:12:31,930 --> 01:12:35,517
I won't forget about you...
Or about...

1021
01:12:35,684 --> 01:12:38,812
We all have to go where
our hearts take us.

1022
01:12:38,896 --> 01:12:41,357
The place that's best for you.

1023
01:12:42,232 --> 01:12:45,694
But what about you, Yui?
You're going to be all alone.

1024
01:12:45,861 --> 01:12:47,905
I can't think that.

1025
01:12:48,072 --> 01:12:51,700
- I know he'll be back.
- He will come back.

1026
01:12:51,867 --> 01:12:54,036
And I know you'll both
be so happy.

1027
01:12:54,203 --> 01:12:56,038
Yeah, we all will.

1028
01:12:58,832 --> 01:13:00,334
[SOFT SOB]

1029
01:13:11,053 --> 01:13:14,181
It's been wonderful. [SOBS]
I've gotta go! [WEEPS]

1030
01:13:16,392 --> 01:13:18,227
[SOFT GASP]

1031
01:13:19,728 --> 01:13:23,023
- [MELANCHOLY POP MUSIC]
- [DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

1032
01:13:49,466 --> 01:13:51,218
[SOFT GASP]

1033
01:13:51,385 --> 01:13:53,429
[CAR STARTS]

1034
01:13:56,849 --> 01:14:00,686
Remember... every moment
that we live is a blessing.

1035
01:14:00,853 --> 01:14:05,399
[SOBS] Goodbye, Mai... Tomomi...

1036
01:14:20,164 --> 01:14:23,125
~i~ \"The Wind's Lullaby,\" ~b~ a new song.

1037
01:14:24,251 --> 01:14:26,837
[GROANS]

1038
01:14:27,504 --> 01:14:34,136
~b~Eve: ~i~Those who are dreaming...
Lips...

1039
01:14:35,637 --> 01:14:42,311
Hesitant hearts... Fingertips...

1040
01:14:43,145 --> 01:14:47,065
Chase the wind...

1041
01:14:47,149 --> 01:14:51,069
and seize hold of love...

1042
01:14:51,153 --> 01:14:58,869
before this blue city crumbles to dust.

1043
01:14:58,952 --> 01:15:06,952
The sky, reflected in building windows...

1044
01:15:07,169 --> 01:15:14,885
wants to bring me to you.

1045
01:15:14,968 --> 01:15:22,968
It's my first morning.

1046
01:15:23,936 --> 01:15:31,109
I want to deliver my heart to you.

1047
01:15:31,193 --> 01:15:35,113
The wind's lullaby-I'll let you listen.

1048
01:15:35,197 --> 01:15:39,159
The wind's lullaby-I'll sing it for you.

1049
01:15:39,243 --> 01:15:44,414
Don't show me...

1050
01:15:44,581 --> 01:15:51,004
- Shogo...
- that sad profile again.

1051
01:16:08,689 --> 01:16:10,983
[GRUNTS AND GROANS]

1052
01:16:27,291 --> 01:16:31,878
[WISTFUL POP MUSIC BEGINS]

1053
01:16:35,299 --> 01:16:42,889
~b~Eve: ~i~I met the city
girl in the \"heart town.\"

1054
01:16:42,973 --> 01:16:47,060
She acted cheerful, but she kept...

1055
01:16:47,144 --> 01:16:51,064
her loneliness inside somewhere.

1056
01:16:51,148 --> 01:16:58,739
I haven't seen her for a while...

1057
01:16:58,822 --> 01:17:06,822
and I heard rumors about her
which bother me.

1058
01:17:08,874 --> 01:17:13,795
[MUSIC BECOMES DYNAMIC]

1059
01:17:21,553 --> 01:17:27,643
I might have another broken heart, again.

1060
01:17:27,726 --> 01:17:33,231
I saw her walking with him.

1061
01:17:33,315 --> 01:17:39,446
When this song plays ever so gently...

1062
01:17:39,529 --> 01:17:47,529
I wonder if we'll
ever be romantic again.

1063
01:18:12,479 --> 01:18:18,568
The smell of a gimlet reminds me of you.

1064
01:18:18,652 --> 01:18:25,117
The cafe bar where you once
whispered lovingly.

1065
01:18:25,200 --> 01:18:31,289
I haven't been there for a while...

1066
01:18:31,373 --> 01:18:39,373
but give me a call right now.

1067
01:18:54,104 --> 01:19:00,235
Loneliness has given me sleepless nights.

1068
01:19:00,318 --> 01:19:05,866
We broke up because of a fight, but...

1069
01:19:05,949 --> 01:19:12,038
when I hear this ever-so-tender song...

1070
01:19:12,122 --> 01:19:19,713
I wonder if you'll return to me smiling.

1071
01:19:19,796 --> 01:19:25,886
When this song plays ever so gently...

1072
01:19:25,969 --> 01:19:32,058
I wonder if we'll
ever be romantic again.

1073
01:19:32,142 --> 01:19:38,231
When I hear this ever-so-tender song...

1074
01:19:38,315 --> 01:19:44,988
I wonder if you'll return to me smiling.

